and title font-weight-lighter" href="/"> Long Chen @ HKUST </a> <button class="navbar-toggler collapsed ml-auto" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbarNav" aria-controls="navbarNav" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation"> <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span> <span class="icon-bar top-bar"></span> <span class="icon-bar middle-bar"></span> <span class="icon-bar bottom-bar"></span> </button> <div class="collapse navbar-collapse text-right" id="navbarNav"> <ul class="navbar-nav ml-auto flex-nowrap"> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/">About </a> </li> <li class="nav-item active"> <a class="nav-link" href="/Join_Us/">Join Us <span class="sr-only">(current)</span> </a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/Publications/">Publications </a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/Teaching/">Teaching &amp; Talks </a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/Students/">Students </a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/Bio/">Biosketch </a> </li> <li class="toggle-container"> <button id="light-toggle" title="Change theme"> <i class="fa-solid fa-moon"></i> <i class="fa-solid fa-sun"></i> </button> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </nav> <progress id="progress" value="0"> <div class="progress-container"> <span class="progress-bar"></span> </div> </progress> </header> <div class="container mt-5" role="main"> <div class="post"> <header class="post-header"> <p class="post-description"></p> </header> <article> <h2 id="information-for-prospective-students-updated-in-202507"><center>Information for Prospective Students (Updated in 2025.07)</center></h2> <p><br></p> <p text-align="center"><b><font color="blue">Research Group:</font></b> <a href="https://long-group.cse.ust.hk/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank"><img src="/assets/img/hkust/long-hkust-logo.png" style="width:200px;"></a> </p> <p> 1. Based on the current funding situation, we have only <font color="red">extremely limited <b>postdocs</b>, <b>research assistants</b>, and <b>visiting students</b> openings</font>. (Please also highlight if you have other funding sources or supports). <br> 2. <font color="green"> As for <b>Ph.D. and M.Phil</b>. positions, we always have the openings all year around</font>. <br> 3. To further increase the diversity, Ph.D./M.Phil applicants from <b>overseas countries</b> and <b>HK</b> are strongly recommended. </p> <hr> <p><img src="../assets/img/hkust/view.jpeg" hspace="20" align="right" style=" width:350px"></p> <p>Thanks for your interest in joining our group. <b>The research interests of our group lie in broad computer vision, machine learning, artificial intelligence, multimedia, and natural language processing</b>. Thus, don’t hesitate to reach out if your only concern is about the research topics. Please read the following information before contacting me.</p> <p><b>I will read every email but I may only reply to those with a good match. Meanwhile, due to the busy schedule, it may take some days/weeks for response. Sorry for the late response and thanks for your time again.</b></p> <p><b><font color="green">Besides, for Hong Kong local students and international students (except Mainland China, Macau, and Taiwan), please also highlight your nationality in the email.</font></b></p> <h4 id="what-i-can-offer-to-you"><b><font color="blue">What I can offer to you?</font></b></h4> <ul> <li>Good research environment consists of innovative research ideas for top-tier conferences/journals, and sufficient computational resources.</li> <li>For junior students, I will provide first-hand research guidance on developing their research skills, eg, weekly meetings which can help them to grow up fast.</li> <li>For senior students/postdocs, I will help you to develop your mentorship and leadership by co-advising some students and leading some projects, which can help them to become independent researchers.</li> <li>For all my students, I will try my best to expand your connections in both academia and industry. Thus, I will refer you to some potential visiting/internship opportunities in top research labs in both companies or other top universities around the world. </li> </ul> <p><b><font color="green">If you have any specific questions about the mentoring styles, a relatively objective solution is asking (by emails) exisitng or past members in our groups. Of course, please remember, everyone has their own bias.</font></b></p> <h4 id="general-requirements"><b><font color="blue">General Requirements</font></b></h4> <ul> <li>Enjoy research</li> <li>Integrity</li> <li>Optimistic and positive life attitude</li> <li>Work smart and self-motivated</li> </ul> <h4 id="phd-students"><b><font color="blue">Ph.D. Students</font></b></h4> <p>The <strong>detailed deadlines</strong> and <strong>basic English language admission requirements</strong> for the Ph.D. applications at HKUST can be found on the official website: <a href="https://prog-crs.hkust.edu.hk/pgprog/2024-25/mphil-phd-cse" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">https://prog-crs.hkust.edu.hk/pgprog/2024-25/mphil-phd-cse</a>.</p> <p><b><font color="red">Important!</font> For students who need HK visa, the deadline for sending PhD offer:</b></p> <ul> <li>Fall semester round: The end of May in the same year (e.g., For 2026 Fall, ddl is 2026 May.)</li> <li>Spring semester round: The the end of Nov. in the previous year (e.g., For 2026 Spring, ddl is 2025 Nov.)</li> </ul> <p><strong>The deadline for HKPFS (<a href="https://cerg1.ugc.edu.hk/hkpfs/index.html" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Hong Kong PhD Fellowship</a>) application is the end of Nov.</strong></p> <p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p> <ul> <li> <strong>For master students</strong>, you should at least have one first-author (or co-first author) publication in top-tier CV/ML/AI/NLP conferences or journals.</li> <li> <strong>For undergraduate students</strong>, you should show your strong learning ability, such as a high GPA ranking among your cohort. Students with rich research experience (such as research publications or internship experience) or excellent coding ability are preferred.</li> </ul> <p>Any interested candidates just directly send an email to me. It would be better to describe your motivations in the email (especially why you think we’d be a good match). The subject for your inquiry email can be <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">[PhD -- YEAR Fall/Spring –- YOUR UNIVERSITY NAME -- YOUR NAME]</code> (e.g., [PhD – 2026 Fall – MIT – Long]). <b><font color="red">For attachment, you should contain:</font></b></p> <ul> <li> <strong>Your CV</strong> (including all intern experiences or publications, if any)</li> <li> <strong>Undergraduate transcripts</strong> (highlight your GPA rank with perceptage in CV),</li> <li> <strong>reference letters or NAME of YOUR REFEREES</strong> (strongly recommended, if someone can evaluate your ability)</li> </ul> <h4 id="mphil-students"><b><font color="blue">M.Phil Students</font></b></h4> <p>MPhil application follow the same standard and requirement as the PhD student. The only difference is that <strong>you must be an undergraduate student</strong>.</p> <h4 id="visiting-students"><b><font color="blue">Visiting Students</font></b></h4> <p>We always welcome visiting students for a wide range of collaboration. However, <strong>due to the funding situation and limited resource, the openings for visiting student are limited.</strong> <b><font color="red">Meanwhile, please remember, it will take around 2 months for visa application.</font></b></p> <p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Typically, for visiting students, you should be a current Ph.D./master/undergraduate student in another university.</li> <li>The duration is typically 6 months.</li> <li> <strong>For PhD/master student</strong>, you should have at least one first-author publication in mainstream top-tier CV/ML/AI/NLP conferences and journals.</li> </ul> <p>Any interested candidates can directly send me <b><font color="red">your CV and representative publications (if any), and transcripts (for undergraduate students)</font></b> by email. <strong>Please highlight the source funding support in the email, such as the funding from my part (HKUST) or other agencies (such as your own university)</strong>. It would be better to shortly introduce how your research matches or complements our group’s research interests. The subject for your inquiry email can be <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">[Visiting -- YOUR UNIVERSITY NAME —- YOUR NAME -- DURATION -- STARTING TIME]</code> (e.g. [Visiting – MIT – Long – 6 months – 2026 Jan]).</p> <h4 id="postdocs"><b><font color="blue">Postdocs</font></b></h4> <p>First of all, Hong Kong government proivdes some postdoc fellowship, which can support postdocs (Please remember, the application deadline is the end of every Oct.)</p> <ul> <li>RGC Junior Research Fellow Scheme (JRFS)</li> <li>Jockey Club Global STEM Postdoctoral Fellowship</li> </ul> <p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Ph.D. degree in computer science, electrical engineering, or related fields, with relevant specialization.</li> <li>Strong record of first-author publication in mainstream top-tier CV/AI/NLP conferences or journals.</li> <li>Proficient in English. Strong written and verbal communication skills.</li> </ul> <p>The typical duration for a postdoc is at least 1 year. Of course, we can further discuss extending the contract if you are planning to stay longer. Any interested candidates can directly send me <b><font color="red">your CV, reference letters, and a research statement</font></b> by email. It would be better to highlight the name of 2-3 your collaborators (such as your Ph.D. advisor or other professors) who can comprehensively evaluate your research ability. The subject for your inquiry email can be <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">[Postdoc – YOUR UNIVERSITY NAME -- YOUR NAME -- STARTING TIME]</code> (e.g. [Postdoc – MIT – Long – 2026 Fall]).</p> <h4 id="current-hkust-students"><b><font color="blue">Current HKUST Students</font></b></h4> <p>For both Msc students and undergraduates, please directly send me <b><font color="red">your CV and transcripts</font></b>. The subject for your inquiry email can be <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">[HKUST -- MS/UG -- YEAR -- NAME]</code> (e.g. [HKUST – UG – Y3 – Long]). Typically, UG students can enroll into the UROP program or FYP/FYT (for Year-4 students).</p> <h4 id="remote-collaborations"><b><font color="blue">Remote Collaborations</font></b></h4> <p>Due to my personal limited time, I usually don’t collaborate with students in a remote way.</p> <hr> </article> </div> </div> <footer class="fixed-bottom" role="contentinfo"> <div class="container mt-0"> © Copyright 2026 Long Chen. </div> </footer> <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jquery@3.6.0/dist/jquery.min.js" integrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSYGSHk7tPXikynS7ogEvDej/m4=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script> <script src="/assets/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script> <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mdbootstrap@4.20.0/js/mdb.min.js" integrity="sha256-NdbiivsvWt7VYCt6hYNT3h/th9vSTL4EDWeGs5SN3DA=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script> <script defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/masonry-layout@4.2.2/dist/masonry.pkgd.min.js" integrity="sha256-Nn1q/fx0H7SNLZMQ5Hw5JLaTRZp0yILA/FRexe19VdI=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script> <script defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/imagesloaded@5.0.0/imagesloaded.pkgd.min.js" integrity="sha256-htrLFfZJ6v5udOG+3kNLINIKh2gvoKqwEhHYfTTMICc=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script> <script defer src="/assets/js/masonry.js" type="text/javascript"></script> <script defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/medium-zoom@1.1.0/dist/medium-zoom.min.js" integrity="sha256-ZgMyDAIYDYGxbcpJcfUnYwNevG/xi9OHKaR/8GK+jWc=" crossorigin="